<item>
            <title>[OAK-10305] oak-core should changes scope of annotation dependencies to provided</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-10305</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently both &lt;tt&gt;org.osgi.service.component.annotations&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;org.osgi.service.metatype.annotations&lt;/tt&gt; have the default scope &lt;tt&gt;compile&lt;/tt&gt; which makes this dependency transitively available to dependent Maven modules. &lt;br/&gt;
As those annotations are only relevant at build time they should always be used with scope &lt;tt&gt;provided&lt;/tt&gt; in order to prevent them to be transitively inherited.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
